The paper proposes a method for reducing computational requirements in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The method involves using decision mechanisms based on differentiable Information Gain, which is a technique commonly used in decision trees. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL), as these are the most relevant sub-categories for research on deep learning and decision trees.
